HEADWORD: Pellmell
<hw>Pell`mell"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>p⟦ecir⟧le-m⟦ecir⟧le</ets>, prob. fr. <ets>pelle</ets> a shovel +
<ets>m⟦ecir⟧ler</ets> to mix, as when different kinds of grain are
heaped up and mixed with a shovel. See <er>Pell</er> shovel,
<er>Medley</er>.]</ety> <def>In utter confusion; with confused
violence.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Men, horses, chariots, crowded
<xex>pellmell</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

